Interface Managed<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type representing the owner.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AmbientLight, Asset, Camera, Entity, GpuShaderProgram.Attribute<T>, GpuShaderProgram.Input<T>, GpuShaderProgram.LocatableInput<T>, GpuShaderProgram.StorageBuffer<T>, GpuShaderProgram.Uniform<T>, Light, ManualObject, SceneNode, SceneObject, SkeletalEntity, SkyBox, Tessellation
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAsset, AbstractGenericSceneObject, AbstractGlslProgramAttribute, AbstractGlslProgramAttributeBuffer, AbstractGlslProgramInput, AbstractGlslProgramLocatableInput, AbstractGlslProgramStorageBuffer, AbstractGlslProgramUniform, Animation, GenericAmbientLight, GenericCamera, GenericEntity, GenericLight, GenericManualObject, GenericSceneNode, GenericSkeletalEntity, GenericSkyBox, GenericTessellation, GlslProgramAttributeBufferVec2, GlslProgramAttributeBufferVec3, GlslProgramAttributeBufferVec4, GlslProgramIndexBuffer, GlslProgramStorageBufferFloat, GlslProgramUniformBool, GlslProgramUniformFloat, GlslProgramUniformInt, GlslProgramUniformMat3, GlslProgramUniformMat4, GlslProgramUniformVec3, GlslProgramUniformVec4, Material, Mesh, Shader, Skeleton, Texture

    public interface Managed<T>
    A managed instance is one that is created by another object that's considered to be its "owner" and whose life-cycle is meant to be controlled by it.
    Author:
    Raymond L. Rivera
